  <title>GLib.DateTime.new_local</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function new_local(year: Number(gint), month: Number(gint), day: Number(gint), hour: Number(gint), minute: Number(gint), seconds: Number(gdouble)): <link xref="GLib.DateTime">GLib.DateTime</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_date_time_new_local()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Creates a new <link xref="GLib.DateTime"/> corresponding to the given date and time in
the local time zone.</p>  <p>This call is equivalent to calling <link xref="GLib.DateTime.new"/> with the time
zone returned by <link xref="GLib.new_local"/>.</p>
  <p>Since 2.26</p>
